    <string name = "pref_foreground_service_title">Foreground Service</string>
    <string name = "pref_foreground_service_summary">Piccolo works by using a service. Services
                                                    run in the background on your phone. A foreground
                                                    service displays a persistent notification to let you know
                                                    it is active and the service will never be killed. Alternatively
                                                    a normal service can be used which does not display a persistent
                                                    notification but the service is then vulnerable to being killed
                                                    by the android operating system
                                                    (e.g. because of low memory) and will be restarted when
                                                    possible.
